Comment:
 The BPF translation unit is dual-licensed for kernel-ABI reasons.
 Linux's license_is_gpl_compatible() allowlist does not recognize the
 literal string "AGPL", and most tracing helpers iomoments uses are
 GPL-only. The GPL-2.0-only branch unlocks those helpers at verifier
 load; the AGPL-3.0-or-later branch keeps the project license identity
 consistent. See COPYRIGHT and DECISIONS.md (D001) for the full
 rationale.

